Use the standard library
This is how to words_string of s:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that current is ""
   Remember that n is s's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that c is item i in s
      Remember that sep is 0
      When c is 32, then:
         Remember that sep is 1
      End when
      When c is 44, then:
         Remember that sep is 1
      End when
      When sep is 1, then:
         When current's length is more than 0, then:
            Add result to current
            Remember that current is ""
         End when
      But, if not:
         Add current to c
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   When current's length is more than 0, then:
      Add result to current
   End when
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> words_string of "" 
[]
>>> words_string of "Hi, my name is John" 
["Hi", "my", "name", "is", "John"]
>>> words_string of "One, two, three, four, five, six" 
["One", "two", "three", "four", "five", "six"]
>>> words_string of "hello world" 
["hello", "world"]
>>> words_string of "a,b,c" 
["a", "b", "c"]